Building MUSCLE üèãüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

happy sunday babes! pulled a muscle in my back the other day so I've been resting up ‚ù§Ô∏è got a ton of questions about how to put on muscle in my story q+a so here's some tips that helped me put on the gains I've been working for.

BUILDING muscle (hypertrophy) üí™üèº requires overloading the muscles with resistance training - this didn't happen by doing cardio. I aim for 4-5 sessions a week split between full body, lower and upper body. lower body starts with compound lifts like sumo deadlifts, barbell squats and finish off with glute, hamstring and quad work üëèüèº
upper body involves compound lifts like press's, pull downs, rows and isolating the smaller muscle groups. for both lower and upper I focus on strength (lifting heavy 6-8 reps) and muscle conditioning (12-20 reps)

FUELLING your body means to EAT üçë if you want to grow, eating in a surplus is necessary üíØ 
I have a hard time putting on weight so gains happened slow, it seemed no matter how much I ate.. I should eat more but with a small appetite this can be difficult.
day by day I changed my eating habits and steadily increased calories by eating more protein, carbs and healthy fats at each meal which helped put on more muscle mass. I also add a high calorie vegan protein shake on my training days to get in additional cals!

it pushed me out of my comfort zone.. but good things happen when you get out of your comfort zone üôèüèº
hope this gave you some motivation to smash your workouts this upcoming week babes

Sunday's with my so called angel üòà

You guys seemed to like my self reflective post this week and it feel's like a good day for another!
I get asked about motivation all the time.
How do you stay so motivated? 
GURL well.. I don't
I struggle with being consistent and staying motivated, some days I have to find the energy to get myself out of bed. 
I start my day with a few mantra's to help concentrate on my 'WHY' and my happiness. It works for me and helps get my motivation back up!

Here's a few:
take charge of your life
let go off stress, it's a new day
you're stronger than you think

I also take my pooch on walks/hikes, do yoga and meditate to help me get into a motivated mindset. 
If your struggling with motivation - try mantra's out and use words that you need for a boost. hope this gave you a new outlook on how to start your day!
